OL,3,C'The sound of the car hitting people
OL,4,Cwill live with me forever'
OL,6,FA mother described how she thought her
OL,7,Fbaby son had died after his pram was
OL,8,Fthrown into the air after being hit by
OL,9,FPaul Doyle's car, adding she thought
OL,10,Fshe would "be next".
OL,12,FSheree Aldridge, 37, said her partner
OL,13,FDan Eveson had dressed their six-month-
OL,14,Fold son Teddy Eveson in his Liverpool
OL,15,FFC shirt that day and "was excited to
OL,16,Fshare this moment" with him.
OL,18,FHer statement read: "In that moment I
OL,19,Fthought I was going to die. I didn't
OL,20,Fknow where Dan and Teddy was.
